### 8. KEY FINDINGS FOR ADMINISTRATION FEATURE

**Already exists and ready**:
- Admin role distinction (ADMIN role)
- User enable/disable (active boolean on User)
- Role management endpoint (PUT /api/admin/users/{id}/roles)
- User status endpoint (PUT /api/admin/users/{id}/status)
- Category CRUD admin endpoints (POST, PUT, DELETE /api/admin/categories)
- User listing with search (GET /api/admin/users?search=...)
- Comprehensive role-based access control via SecurityConfig and @PreAuthorize

**Missing for full Administration feature**:
- **No comment moderation**: Comments lack status/approved flags; hard-deleted only. Admin cannot soft-delete or flag.
- **No content moderation**: Posts have status (DRAFT/PUBLISHED) but no "FLAGGED" or "UNDER_REVIEW" state.
- **No platform statistics endpoint**: No aggregate endpoint for total posts/users/comments/engagement metrics.
- **No user activity audit**: No audit log of admin actions (who disabled whom, when).
- **No user suspension/ban**: active flag is binary; no temporary suspension or duration tracking.
- **No comment author block**: Users cannot block others; admins can only hard-delete.
- **No post visibility control beyond status**: Published posts are public; no "unlisted" state.

**Recommendation for implementation**:
1. Extend Comment entity with `status` (APPROVED, FLAGGED, DELETED) and `moderation_flag_reason`
2. Extend Post entity with `moderation_status` (optional)
3. Create CommentModerationController with admin endpoints (GET flagged comments, PATCH to approve/reject)
4. Create PlatformStatisticsController with admin endpoints for dashboards
5. Create AuditLog entity and service for admin action tracking
6. Consider optio for user suspension (end_suspension_at Instant field)

All this has existing infrastructure (SecurityConfig roles, repository patterns, DTO mappings, test patterns) to build upon.</result>
